图片来源：图虫来源：湖北省政府网站“ 湖北省政府网站3月12日在防控科普栏目中发布一篇来自华中科技大学同济医院的文章。
2007-9-25 21: 48 Hubei provincial government website www.hubei provincial government on March 12 in the prevention and control of science and technology column from the Tongji Hospital of Huazhong University of Science and Technology.
”编者按：湖北省政府网站3月12日在防控科普栏目中发布一篇来自华中科技大学同济医院的文章。
According to the editor, the website of Hubei Provincial Government published an article from Tongji Hospital of Huazhong University of Science and Technology on March 12.
文章称，华中科技大学同济医院生殖医学中心李豫峰教授团队提醒：感染新冠肺炎的适龄男性，在康复后应进行生育力检查。
Professor Li Henfeng, professor of reproductive medicine at Tongji Hospital in Huazhong University of Science and Technology, warned that men of the right age infected with pneumonia should undergo fertility testing after recovery.
以下为文章全文新型冠状病毒感染以肺脏和免疫系统损害为主，但理论上新冠感染还可能造成睾丸损伤。
The following is the full text of the new coronavirus infection mainly lung and immune system damage, but in theory the new crown infection may also cause testicular damage.
因此，华中科技大学同济医院生殖医学中心李豫峰教授团队提醒：感染新冠肺炎的适龄男性，在康复后应进行生育力检查。
Therefore, Professor Li Henfeng, professor of reproductive medicine at Tongji Hospital of Huazhong University of Science and Technology, warned that male age-appropriate patients with new crown pneumonia should undergo fertility testing after recovery.
新型冠状病毒通过刺突糖蛋白（S蛋白）与宿主细胞血管紧张素转化酶2（ACE2）结合从而入侵细胞，引起组织损伤。
The new coronavirus can invade cells and cause tissue damage by binding to host cell angiotensin converting enzyme 2 (ACE2).
除肺以外，人体很多其他器官也表达ACE2，如睾丸、小肠、肾脏、心脏和甲状腺等。
In addition to the lungs, many other organs in the body also express ACE2, such as the testicles, small intestine, kidneys, heart and thyroid.
其中，睾丸表达大量的ACE2，主要集中在睾丸精原细胞、支持细胞和间质细胞，这几种细胞均与男性生殖功能密切相关。
Among them, testicular expression of a large number of ACE2, mainly concentrated in testicular spermatogonia, supporting cells and stromal cells, all of which are closely related to male reproductive function.
生曲细精管又叫生精小管，是精子生成的场所，内有各级生精细胞和支持细胞，曲细精管之间含有间质细胞。
The seminiferous tubing, also known as spermatozoon, is the site of sperm production. It contains spermatogenic cells and supporting cells.
精原细胞是形成精子的前体细胞；支持细胞对于维持精子发育的微环境至关重要，成年人的支持细胞不再分裂，数量恒定；间质细胞则是合成和分泌雄激素的主要细胞，雄激素可促进精子发生和男性生殖器官发育，以及维持男性第二性征和性功能。
Sperm cells are progenitor cells that form sperm; supporting cells are essential to the microenvironment that sustains sperm development. Adult support cells do not divide and remain constant; interstitial cells are the main cells for the synthesis and secretion of androgen, which promotes spermatogenesis and male genital development, as well as the maintenance of secondary sexual characteristics and functions in men.
尽管目前尚无研究证实新冠病毒感染是否损伤睾丸及影响男性生育能力，但新冠病毒与SARS病毒高度相似，其感染入侵细胞受体相同，即ACE2。
Although there are no studies that confirm whether a new crown virus infection damages the testicles and affects male fertility, the new crown virus is highly similar to the SARS virus, with the same number of invading cell receptors, ACE2.
尽管未在睾丸中检测出SARS病毒，但SARS感染仍可导致睾丸出现严重的免疫性损伤，引起睾丸炎，并造成生殖相关细胞广泛破坏。
Although no SARS virus has been detected in the testicles, the SARS infection can cause severe immune damage to the testicles, cause testicular inflammation and cause widespread destruction of reproductive-related cells.
所以从理论上推测，新冠感染可能造成睾丸损伤，影响精子生成和雄激素合成。
Theoretically, therefore, new crown infections may cause testicular damage, affecting sperm production and androgen synthesis.
精子生成受阻会影响男性生育能力，严重者可能导致男性不育；雄激素不足会影响男性第二性征和性功能，降低生活质量。
Impaired sperm production can affect male fertility and, in some cases, male infertility; insufficient androgen deficiency can affect secondary sexual characteristics and function in men and reduce the quality of life.
因此，对于有感染病史的男性，尤其是有生育需求的男性，最好在康复后进行精液质量和激素水平等生育力相关检查，以便及时发现问题尽早处理。
Therefore, for men with a history of infection, especially men with reproductive needs, fertility-related tests, such as semen quality and hormone levels, are best performed after rehabilitation in order to detect problems as early as possible.
